<br>
Once you get higher up, mana/hp is not so insanely fast either.<br>
<br>
Not sure how you say its less challenging than EQ, how is it any less challenging then sitting killing greens for hours waiting for named_mob_03 to spawn? AI is immensely smarter in DAoC the EQ, and pets actually follow your exact path too ;P<br>
<br>
Also, you lose your buffs when the person dies since they use the concentration skill, not mana, to maintain your buffs...kinda hard to keep concentrating when you are dead.<br>
<br>
Interface is kind of odd at first, but that is just because it is new to ya...its all second nature to me now, learning curve on the interface seems easier to learn to me then EQ did. Only thing I miss is the mouse look with the right mouse key.<br>
<br>
RvR is not really a zerg rush, well it is in the extent that you have to zerg rush the archer (since they are gods in RvR).<br>
<br>
It sucks that all the rogue classes (shadowblade, infiltrator and nightshade) blow. <br>
<br>
I got a new system recently and the game is not slow at all, and the quietness is Realm dependent pretty much...Midgard is awesome for getting groups and meeting people, real sense of camraderie there (and all seem to be ex-EQ players). Albion seems to be 'first character' realm in both to the game and mmorpgs in general. Hibernia is filled with lots of folks that are clueless about life in general in addition to the game.<br>
<br>
EQ is based off of old MUDS and they added all the annoying factors like binding, massive downtime, camps, etc., Camelot is built under a different philosophy in that its a game and should be enjoyable, not feel like a job.<br>
<br>
Besides, the way I see it, if I played camelot first, then EQ came out and I wanted to try it and had to put up with spending an hour looking for a bind, losing my corpse, screwed up tradeskills, massive exp loss for death, fighting over spawns, possibility of endless hours looking for a group in order to do anything, needing to dedicate a 4-5 hour period of time once I get into a group...I would never try EQ.<br>
<br>
UO is a waste since 'Lord British' left...I will never buy another Ultima based game again. Beta tested AC for awhile, I still think thats the worst online game out there with the exception of AO where you pay 10 bucks a month to play a single player game with no content.<br>
<br>
Camelot had my interest since I first heard about, has exceeding my expectations since its been out. I have absolutely no desire to even log on to EQ, let alone continuing to pay Sony for, in my opinion, an inferior product with poor customer service, poor AI, and the current 'Monty Haul' mentality.<br>
<br>
Ah well, gaming styles and choices are a personal decision, and I choose camelot over EQ. <br>
<br>
-Darryn<br>
